President Biden visited Lewiston, Maine, after a tragic shooting incident that took place at a bowling alley. He expressed his condolences and support to the community, acknowledging the trauma experienced by first responders, healthcare workers, survivors, and the families of the victims. The President emphasized the need for unity and honest conversations about gun violence prevention. He called for common-sense measures to protect people's freedom to go about their daily lives without fear of being shot. President Biden closed his speech with a prayer for the healing of those affected and praised the resilience and unity demonstrated by the community. Senator Collins also spoke at the event.